DIPHTHERIA - PHILIPPINES: INCREASED CASES, FOUR REGIONS
*******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 14 Dec 2018
Source: Manila Bulletin [edited]
https://news.mb.com.ph/2018/12/14/doh-increase-in-diphtheria-cases-seen-in-bicol-davao-regions-soccksargen-armm/


The Department of Health (DOH) reported that diphtheria cases have increased in 4 regions. The DOH-Epidemiology Bureau said that the increase in diphtheria cases were seen in Bicol region, Davao region, Soccsksargen, and the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao (ARMM).

Soccsksargen had registered the highest increase, 200%, from one case in 2017 to 3 cases this year [2018]. It was followed by Bicol region, with a 167% increase (3 cases in 2017 to 8 cases in 2018), while ARMM (6 cases in 2017 to 12 cases in 2018) and Davao region (3 cases in 2017 to 6 cases in 2018) both registered a 100% increase.

The DOH, meanwhile, noted that diphtheria cases nationwide had decreased. For this year [2018], there were only 147 diphtheria cases as compared to the 168 cases recorded during the previous year [2017]. The health department also noted that the number of deaths also decreased, from 41 in 2017 to 34 this year [2018].

[Byline: AnalOu De Vera]

